  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its size and location, would fail to comply with the 45-degree rule in relation to a ground-floor window at 53 Walford Road. As such, it would have a harmful impact on the amenities enjoyed by these residents in regard to loss of outlook, sense of enclosure, and loss of daylight/sunlight. The proposed development is, therefore, considered unacceptable and fails to comply with policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021), policies LP1 and LP2 of the Hackney Local Plan LP33 (2020), and the stipulations of the council&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its incongruous design, location, and inappropriate materiality, would appear at odds with the character of the immediate area and would disrupt the sense of symmetry across the rear elevations of the application site and adjoining property of no. 53 Walford Road. The proposed development is, therefore, considered unacceptable and fails to comply with policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021), LP1 of the Hackney Local Plan LP33 (2020), and the stipulations of the council&#x27;s Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
